  sodium: 640 mg
---

Arrange rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice
@bell pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice
@red onion{1} into 1-inch pieces. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes, bell pepper, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle
of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until crisp and
tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Transfer roasted veggies to a #plate{} and let cool for at least
~{5%minutes}.

When ready to serve, in a large #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} with
half the @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce} (save the rest for serving).

Divide mixed greens between plates; pile roasted veggies over top and
drizzle with remaining vinaigrette. Garnish with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}
and parsley. Serve immediately.